The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Ropeway across river

 Calcutta, July 17: The tourism department is planning ropeways up to Darjeeling and across the Hooghly in Calcutta, minister Manab Mukherjee said today.

 Promising a draft tourism policy soon, Mukherjee told the Assembly a private agency has been entrusted with the job of identifying tourist destinations and the need for infrastructure development.

 He also iterated the governments desire to develop tea tourism, beach tourism and a pilgrimage circuit.




